  "texts": [
    "For present purposes, the point made byArmstrong (1971, p. 432), according to which having an intention, as opposed to having an objective, implies being confident to reach the communicative goal in question, is immaterial.",
    "What is central is that NLP models such as BERT are unable to intend anything, confidently or not.123",
    "Indeed, if we remember the way that these generative LLMs are being trained, namely by iteratively acquiring a more accurate ability to predict the next token given the previous tokens, intriguing analogies to clinical free association show up.",
    "See, for instance, Reis (1970), and ultimately Freud (1921).",
    "From a very different perspective, one might argue that these very associative connections that these LLMs acquire during training resemble the fast, intuitive, but perhaps less logically sound mode of thinking in two-process theories, see Kahneman (2003)."
  ],
